SYMPTOM_TEXT: In two neurologic events at one hour and at 13 days after my first dose of the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine, numbness suddenly increased in my body, which already had moderate peripheral neuropathy, resulting in a documented decrease in balance and increase in fall risk. I estimate the vaccine has aged my already damaged nervous system by about 25 years. As I figure out how to safely work my farm with my new limitations, I take time to report my adverse reactions to help my fellow "numbies" avoid similar neurologic damage due to the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine and may you have treatments to reverse it? PRE-EXISTING NEUROLOGIC STATE: moderate, stress-hormone-induced peripheral ganglian neuropathy. Began 2007 in right foot. Diagnosed December 2012 by physician. At time of diagnosis (December 2012), approximately 1% feeling remaining in right foot, more, but farfrom 100%, feeling elsewhere. Just before 1st Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine (mid March 2021), approximately 0.1% feeling in right foot and 0.5 -1% feeling elsewhere. Active, full-time farmer. Physical therapy exercises for left ankle and hammer toe help with balance, but a fall or serious near-fall (requiring PT or bandages) about once a year due to numbness. Able to walk on uneven ground and slippery surfaces and safely recover from slips & gopher holes. Through yoga, no longer slightly incontinent. Able to drive, walk, hike, swim, carry 20lb plants & trash bags on uneven surfaces, heavy gardening live independently, cook, care for own self = normal life! SUNDAY MARCH 21, 2021:  6:13 p.m. First COVID 19 vaccine in left arm. 6:43 p.m. Released from waiting room, nerves feel normal Approx 7:15 pm: At home, seated in midst of preparing dinner: Increase in numbness in left-side of lips & minor left-side of mouth. Approx 7:18 pm: Numbness spreads to right lips and minor right-side of mouth Approx 7:20 pm: Tingling begins on lips and minor mouth, maybe more on the right side Approx 7:25 pm: minor "popping" in each ear, like when driving up a mountain, once in each ear Approx 8:30 p.m-10p.m.: seated at home computer doing bookkeeping. Tingling in feet, especially right foot. When I walk around, right knee seems very numb MONDAY MARCH 22, 2021: (morning after vaccine) Approx6am.: Very numb in right foot, right ankle, right calf, and right knee. Maybe 0.001% feeling remaining. A decrease of 99% in 12hours. My most sudden decrease ever! Test my balance by standing on one leg. For the first time in my recollection, my balance is worse on my right leg than my left leg (left ankle prone to sprains). I am alarmed, but event is similar to the many numbing events I have had before (except the lip part rear part). Start calling docs once their offices open. Neurologist out of town. Continue normal work at farm, but slower and extra careful on uneven surfaces. TUESDAY MARCH 23, 2021: (2 days after vaccine) Phone appointment with internist. Recomends my getting the 2nd vaccine in 3weeks. WEDNESDAY MARCH 31, 2021: (10 days after vaccine) In-person appointment with orthopedic foot and ankle surgeon for new numbness, the usual left ankle, 2020 hammertoes and January 2021 near fall. Wrote physical therapy eval/treatment prescription for balance THURSDAY APRIL 1, 2021: (11 days after vaccine) In-person physical therapy eval for balance by physical therapist (test reports enclosed) SATURDAY APRIL 3, 2021: (13 days after vaccine) Unusual numbing even for me. Working at farm in office. Walking normally and turning left into hallway (slightly leaning towards the left like a motorcycle turning), I suddenly release about 1 teaspoon of urine (unusual for me). At first I thought my bladder must be full (I have almost no sensation for the need to urinate), but as I sat on the toilet only a few tablespoons to a quarter cup flow out. Thinking that maybe the left turn has put something out of whack, I did my three most reliable, safe, gentle, work-appropriate exercises: yoga's uttanasana (forward bend on ledge), yoga's utthita trikonasana (triangle pose), PT stroke recovery's marching with opposite arm swings. Instead of helping, within half an hour of the urine leak, my whole right side was pretty much completely numb (0.0001% feeling) Approximately 0.01% feeling on left side. THURSDAY APRIL 8th, 2020 (18 days after vaccine) Phone appointment with neurologist. Concerned about possible nerve delamination. Brain and partial spine MRI scheduled for Monday April 26, in-person follow up scheduled for Wednesday May 5th. Doc or I will provide VAERS with updates APRIL 6, 12, 13, 14: Caught myself just before begining to fall. I am getting so little signal from my nerves that I have to rely mostly on sight, musclememory, and paying attention to walking & standing. PT had suggested walking farm, but they bother my tennis elbow and at my farm I often need to carry a plant of box or something from here to there. If numbness stays the same or gets worse, I would not feel safe farming unless I could modify many aspects of growing areas & parking areas (both asphalt & gophery grass) and had high level orchid grower help plus some just physical work help. APRIL 12th: Public swimming pool is finally open! 15 minutes of PT balance excecises and 25 minutes of freestyle swim and breastroke pull. Afterwards I feel so much better! No change in numbness, but I had no idea how jaded my nerves had been until they finally were calmer. Perhaps this is a hopeful sign that the numbness it temporary. I swim again on Friday the 16th. Let's be hopeful! The End! I will fax in updates unless you provide a more specific contact method
OTHER_MEDS: Synthroid 11%, vitamin D, vitamin B complex, alphal.policacid, algee oil, calcium, psyllium
HISTORY: progressive ganglion neuropathy bodywide, hypothyroid (Graves, 1993), mitrovalve prolapse

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 03/12/2021: Discussion/Summary: Called Patient's Wife regarding Patient's Alprazolam 0.5mg and advised her the Prior Authorization has been completed. And that Insurance responded "Available without Prior Authorization." Also that this page was printed out and faxed to Patient's Pharmacy. Patient's wife stated she greatly appreciated this.   Patient's wife went on to say the both she and Patient received their 1st Covid 19 Vaccine (Pfizer) on 3/5/21. An when Patient left the Pharmacy he was fine. But a little later his Tongue started to swell and the next day his mouth was covered in Blisters. She stated his breathing was okay, but he also had a fever, diarrhea and generalized fatigued. She went on to say that Patient has laid in the bed from Friday night 3/5/21  straight through to Wednesday 3/10/21. She stated has decreased appetite as well.   Inquired of patient's wife if she called to have Patient tested for the Covid 19 virus. She stated "nobody tole me to." Advised patient's wife was just inquiring about that and if she had called to see if Patient could be seen for these symptoms. She replied no.   Advised patient's wife to watch Patient and if needed she can call the clinic After hours Nurse Line or call back on Monday if he continues to be so Fatigued that all he can do is lay around. Patient's wife did state some of the other symptoms have resolved, the blisters in the mouth, swollen tongue, but Patient did experience these for 3 to 4 days after being vaccinated with his 1st Covind 19 (Pfizer) vaccine.  Patient's wife asked should Patient get second one, and the Pharmacist told her "no." Advised patient's wife, Patient needs to discuss this with Dr., or PA.   Advised patient's wife to call if needed for Patient and to please follow up on this Covid 19 after effects on Patient.  Patient's wife voiced understanding. Dr.   03/16/2021: Discussion/Summary: Called back today for follow up with Patient for his reported 1st Covid Vaccine Reaction. (See Care Team Note dated 3/12/21 for documentation).  Spoke with Wife, first. advised her per Nursing Supervisor, even if Patient is better, he needs to come in and have his reaction documented for the Adverse Reporting for the Covid 19 Vaccine. Patient's wife stated she would hand the phone over to Patient.  Inquired of Patient how he was doing and if the "fatigue" he reported from his 1st Covid 19 vaccine had resolved. He stated "I'm always tired, but I am able to go to the Eye doctor this morning." Advised Patient even though he is feeling better and his symptoms he reported (swollen tongue, mouth covered in blisters, so fatigued unable to get out of bed, fever, diarrhea, but breathing was ok), he needs to come in and have this documented so it can be reported to the Adverse Reporting for the Covid 19 Vaccine. Offered Patient appointment today or tomorrow with PA.  He stated he will come in today @ 1:45pm for this visit.   Patient is scheduled for 1:45pm today to follow up on Adverse Reaction to 1st Covid 19 vaccine, per Patient & Wife's reported symptoms. Dr.   03/16/2021: History of Present Illness:  Patient received his first COVID 19 vaccine on March 5.  He had the Pfizer vaccine around 5:00 that afternoon. He was in bed-by 9:00 that evening. He remained in bed through March 7. He developed some nausea,  swelling of his tongue, and mouth ulcers. The tongue swelling resolved by March 10. He also was aware of some palpitations the night after his vaccine. He had no swelling of his airways, shortness of breath, wheezing, fever, chills, headache or increased body aches. He has fibromyalgia, and did not notice any changes in his chronic pain. He complains of ongoing fatigue, but the other symptoms have resolved. He has a history of pulmonary fibrosis which is managed by his pulmonologist, Dr. He was told by Dr. he should not take the second vaccine because of his symptoms following the first vaccine.   Patient had swollen tongue, Blisters in his mouth, Diarrhea, Fatigue, Fever had resolved.   Two weeks ago Patient had "red raised areas wit a clear head," come up on both legs. The left is much worse than Right. No itching, burning, just the raised areas. Patient did "pop" one of them and it still didn't dry up.  Still dealing with Severe Fatigue and this reaction has caused his Fibromyalgia to Flare.   Feels sure he had Fever on 4/13/21. Offered Appointment (See documentation) Seeing Primary Care Provider on 5/3/21.   Advised to call this office with, continued or worsening symptoms.  Patient did voice understanding.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Injection site sore still, radiating joint and muscle pain (hands, arms, shoulder), headaches, fever up to 100.8 >24hrs, body aches,  tingling on the face, tiring, insomnia, mouth sores
Blurry vision, dizziness, weakness.   Has continued and worsened. Can not see to 10 feet, and has worsened to 4 feet. Heart rate 160, unable to function
LAB_DATA: 4/14/2021 went to emergency room. ECG was done and reported as irregular. heart rate  dropped to 115 but remained uncomfortable. ER sent him home as things not irregular enough to admit him. ER was not able to address vision loss and light sensitivity except to recommend him to  have an eye exam the next day.  Vision, light sensitivity and pain did not improve over night.  Eye exam dilated his eyes and stated that they were WNL, except " more than usual blood vessels in the eyes for some reason"  Stated that they could not assess the vision loss.  Pt. could not see past 10 feet though and the light sensitivity remained along with the pain. Eye doctor sent him home to wait it out as things were within normal limits.   Pt still can not see now past 4 feet, and can not work or go about daily activities.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Swelling, itching, redness, heat at the injection site appeared over a week after the vaccine was received. The first few days following, I only had pain in my arm and bad headaches. SYMPTOM_TEXT: About 3 weeks after my first dosis of the Pfizer vaccine, I started having constant numbness in both arms, hands and right legs, dizziness, pins and needles, extreme fatigue, lethargy, feeling the pulse of my heart rate in various part so my body in an opressive kind of way like in my throat, under my right breast, in my back on the ribs usually. All these symptoms never subsided and became noticeably worse a few days after my second dosis on April 8th.  My arms are always numb when I get up and become worse when hanging down, of course, but with different intensity.  I am feeling extremely dizzy as I walk around and unstable. Walking feels like the ground is further than it is in a way. I do notice a slight shortness of breath but more of an oppression in the rib cage than panting. I have been avoiding walking far or walking my dogs all together. I am not seeing any improvements even after my visit to the Urgency Care where nothing wrong was found on blood work and EKG. I was told to reduce inflammation with dietary supplement and some vitamins. I cannot work of course and what is a bit frightening now is that I am not improving on day 8 of my second dosis! Same rotation of weird symptoms all day (feeling my blood not circulating normally if that can be described even, numbness, pins and needles in arms, and right leg. Sometimes it affects my right cheek. Dizziness and unstability to walk around. Vision is lower as well. Too weak to do anything constructive.    My legs feel like they are not reliable (never have had that feeling at my age). It is more than feeling like a zombie, it is feeling too weak to do anything and my head is sometimes spinning. The numbness can be painful as a sudden thrust in an arm ( this does not last more than a few seconds).  It has now been going on since week 3 of my first dosis and today is day 7 of my second dosis! I had 0 symptoms on the first 2 weeks of my vaccine, dosis one. Now, I don't see any progress, rather a slight worsening of all the symptoms above. It is freakish not knowing what I have, of course. One can imagine, so stress adds to the mix sometimes during the day. I would not dare to even go walk my dogs now. A short grocery store visit at the most.
LAB_DATA: On April 14, I visited the Urgent Care where they drew blood and performed an EKG and checked for my reflexes. Nothing too strange was found on that day. Just a high count for red cells, which I was told was normal due to the body fighting under the effect of the vaccine.
OTHER_MEDS: Basic multi vitamins for women, vitamin B12, D3 and C that I take infrequently.
CUR_ILL: Adverse reactions to Pfizer were already going on for me at about week 3 into my first dosis. The administration of the second dosis on April 8th, for which I am filing a second report right here, made it worse.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: About 3 hours after receiving the , vaccine on April 5 at 3:15 pm, I had uncontrollable shivers and chills, shaking violently through my whole entire body.  I was freezing cold to the bone.   I felt nauseous and threw up my entire dinner.  That didn't make the nausea go away - I continued to throw up that evening 5 or 6 more times.  The nausea continued the next day making me throw up 3 more times.  And yet the nausea persisted for a whole entire week.  I had a horrible headache that night that has stuck with me these last ten days.  My muscles ached and shot strange pangs through my body.  I was exhausted.  I could not stay awake.  I was so weak and tired.  I had no energy and just laid in bed for a solid four days. My throat hurt, my neck hurt, my head hurt, my arm where the shot went in hurt so bad.  Very strangely, my stomach was constantly bloated and hurt inside like a bad stomach ache - even if I hadn't eaten anything it still bloated and hurt.  The painful stomach lasted seven or eight days.  I had diarrhea for those seven /eight days.  I was completely dehydrated.  The diarrhea lasted way too long - it was difficult to return to work.  The second day after the shot I woke up to my left eye red, like some blood vessels had burst.  It took four or five days for my eye to go back to normal.   my heart has a stabbing feeling randomly all the time now and it is hard to breathe.  I wheeze and cough all the time.  It is very uncomfortable.  This heart issue has persisted the entire time since getting the vaccine.

Day of shot #2 (3/31/21) I experienced nausea in the first 15 minutes and felt confused while driving.  Nausea passed in 2-3 hours and I felt fine.  The next day I felt tired, foggy brain, and dizzy.  Assumed it was from the shot.  Side effects continued/worsened.  4/6/21 I saw my Dr.  She checked me over, labs. found nothing wrong with me.  Likely side effects from Pfizer.  Unlikely that they would last two weeks.  Rx Meclizine for dizziness, which didn't really help.  Now it's Day 15.  Tired and brain fog are gone.  I don't feel as dizzy.  BUT, when I try to drive, I feel QUITE dizzy with blurred vision.  This side effect persists and clearly effects my quality of life.
LAB_DATA: Checked by my Dr.  Labs.  All labs were normal.  Dr. assumed side effects from Pfizer shot #2
OTHER_MEDS: Seroquel, Temezapam, Diazapam, Citerizine, Vitamin D

SYMPTOM_TEXT: In the 3 weeks leading up to February 10th, I became progressively more bloated with fluid in my stomach area, with an increasing feeling of fullness.  By the 10th, I felt so full that I had only eaten one meal in two days.  I had also been sleeping upright for days to attempt to clear what I perceived to be a stomach blockage and therefore was quite tired.  I walked in to the ER and the x-ray revealed the blood clot in my portal vein.  The physician immediately had enoxaparin administered to me and I was admitted.  I received another enoxaparin dose the next morning.  I was discharged on Xarelto 15mg twice a day in the afternoon of Feb 11th.  I am continuing on Xarelto as my hematologist runs various tests and I have an EGD on 4/16 due to a possible stomach ulcer.  I was diagnosed with: Mesenteric venous thrombosis Elevated transaminase measurement Fatty liver

28 hours after 2nd Pfizer vaccine administered:   First symptom was inability to suck from a straw.  Lips could not be closed together on left side of mouth.  Second symptom noticed was left eye not blinking or closing all the way compared to right eye.   Third symptom was drooping smile on left side of face.   We did not connect the timing of vaccine to this event until the following morning.  It was Saturday morning and the symptoms still existing.  We observed and monitored through the weekend and called the Doctor's office on Monday.  The Doctor asked us to go to Emergency Room right away for possible stroke.
LAB_DATA: The ER Doctor performed a test to check facial nerve function (lift eyebrows, blink eyes, smile).  Since all 3 tests failed, the ER Doctor concluded this is a case of Bell's Palsy.  No further tests were performed other than standard blood pressure, heart rate and oxygen sufficiency (all normal).     5 day course of Prednisone steroid and the anti-viral medicine, Acyclovir were prescribed.

I was 21 weeks pregnant at the time. I experienced a brief episode of vertigo on 1/28/2021, and had a return of the vertigo on 2/4/2021 that lasted all day.  I called my OBGYN thinking it could be pregnancy-related, and was referred to OB triage for monitoring and treatment with IV fluids and Zofran. I made another trip to OB triage on 4/8/2021 for the same reason. The symptoms would fluctuate in severity but never let up, and I?m still dealing with episodes of dizziness to this day. I?ve seen specialists including a neurologist, ENT specialist, audiologist, and am currently in weekly vestibular therapy for my symptoms. Ultimately, I?ve been given a differential diagnosis of vestibular neuritis vs vestibular migraine. I may have been experiencing BPPV when the symptoms began, as well. A neurologist I work closely with believes the symptoms I?ve experienced could be relayed to the COVID-19 vaccine (2nd dose was received on 1/22/2021).

I started taking Acetaminophen 10 mg bid. 4 days on 4/11 till today after first dose  for both pain control and reducing body temperature.  I used to have granulomatous mastitis on my right breast which is self limited and I had not have this problem for one year. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Received vaccine approx 11:20am, no issues until 10:30pm when I started to feel chilled. I took my temp with a forehead thermometer and it read 98.x. I put the thermometer on my nightstand thinking it prudent to have it handy. In bed under covers I kept feeling cold and started shivering/teeth chattering, within an hour or so my forehead thermometer read 102. My recollection of the time between midnight and 2 to 3am is vague as I was very disoriented, I recall taking my forehead temp several times during those hours - that took a lot of effort, and I saw several readings of 105 and I believe one over 106. I remember thinking I should be in the ER, then thinking how could I get there, then thinking I would call 911 but that I could probably not get my mind/body to be able to physically make a phone call. I believe that during this time span I had brief periods of consciousness when I was somewhat aware that I was having a high fever event, but that there wasn't much I could do about it (I live alone). By 4am I was more aware, forehead temp reading was 102.something - I got up and made my way to the kitchen, I was unsteady on my feet and remember telling myself to be careful and not to fall. Temp gradually dropped throughout Tuesday, mostly back to normal on Wed.
OTHER_MEDS: Prevacid, Inderal, Mirapex, Lipitor, Baclofen, Lipitor, Low Dose Naltrexone (4.5 mg), Vitamin D3, St. Johns Wort, CoQ10

I began experiencing severe tinnitus about 9 days after my first Moderna vaccine dose. Very loud electronic hissing tone throughout my head. This has not subsided since March 22. It is ongoing, 24 hours a day. This produced distress, discomfort, and anxiety. I went to the ER at Hospital on March 22 due to the sudden tinnitus onset and the accompanying anxiety. They gave me referrals for an audiologist, PCP, and psychiatrist. At the hospital, they gave me Ativan.  The tinnitus is very uncomfortable, scary, loud, and disruptive. I've had two separate audiologists test my hearing and examine my ears and both are fine. Nothing remarkable. I've also had an MRI done with normal results. I've been to my PCP, another doctor at the same clinic, and an ENT doctor. I also went to a psychiatric physician's assistant. No one seems to know the cause or what to do. I've been prescribed 20 mg of fluoxetine daily, o.5 mg alprazolam as needed for distress. Also prescribed, 25 mg amitriptyline, and 50mg trazodone to help sleep. The trazodone had no effect so I stopped it. Also prescribed a 6-day course of methylprednisolone, but I had to stop on the third day because it kept me up for almost three days, so I stopped. I'm also taking daily Zyrtec, Benadryl, generic multi-symptom allergy medication, 2000mg Vitamin C, B12, and two Chinese herbs. I've also been seeing a chiropractor 3 x a week. I've seen a craniosacral therapist once and will start acupuncture this Sat.
LAB_DATA: I had an MRI with contrast done at Radiological Association on 4/7. It came back with unremarkable results.
OTHER_MEDS: Generic multi-symptom allergy medication as needed Advil as needed

04/14/2021 Noticed around 1:00 p.m. that my left eyelid was sagging.  Concerned it may be a symptom of a stroke, I rushed to the emergency room at Hospital.   They admitted me and ran a variety of tests, one of which was an MRI which concluded that I had not had a stroke.  The neurologist stated that it appeared to be similar to a wrinkle.  Not sure what caused that sudden event.  Possibly a side affect of the COVID `19  shot.   Therefore the report.  I returned home the next day, 04/15/2021.
On April 16th at 1:00AM I woke up to pain in my left foot.   When I got up to take a look I was unable to put full weight on my left foot.  The side of my foot by the small toe is red and swollen.

7pm started feeling symptoms of fever, chills, eyes burning, but temp was 98.2. By 9pm severe chills, involuntary shaking, teeth chattering, still 98.2. Unable to relax due to chills & shaking. 1am got up & retook temperature currently 100.2. Eyes hurt & red, freezing, and goosebumps. Achy & uncomfortable. Headache. Still continuing.
Rapid onset left shoulder aching pain radiating to elbow.  Persists after 1 month with waxing and waning.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Client was vaccinated with the Pfizer Covid vaccine with lot #EW0162 at 11:59am on 04/15/2021. EMT observed client standing at the facility exit speaking to the interpreter.  EMT noted upon approach client appeared alert, tracking with his eyes, in no apparent distress. Client had a chief complaint of numbness at his injection site. Client stated that he had completed his 15 minutes and had exited the site but began to experience numbness at his injection site while exiting. This was the client's first dose of the Pfizer vaccine. Client states he has a history of a deep vein thrombosis and hypertension. Client is not on any medications and denies any known allergies. Assessment revealed that client's left arm/injection site was clean, dry and bandage remained intact. Client was negative for hives, swelling, severe sweating, shortness of breath or other signs of anaphylaxis. Client was alert and oriented to person, place, date, and event; and airway, breathing and circulation were intact. Client had full range of motion of his arm and denied any tingling. Client denied any pain upon palpation of the injection site and stated that his numbness was strictly localized to injection site and did not spread to rest of arm. Client's vital signs upon entering EMT station for further evaluation revealed: blood pressure 180/140, respirations 18, pulse 68, 98% on room air; lung sounds clear bilaterally, temp 98 degrees F, eyes remained equal, round, and reactive to light at 5 mm. Client stated that he had his blood pressure taken last week and that his systolic was approximately 160. Client agreed to remain for an additional 30 minutes of monitoring per site lead nurse and was stable throughout observation. Vital signs at 1220: blood pressure of 180/140, respiratory rate of 18, heart rate of 68, and oxygen saturation of 98% on room air. Vital signs at 1235: blood pressure of 160/124, respiratory rate of 18, heart rate of 76, and oxygen saturation of 99% on room air. Vital signs at 1250: blood pressure of 158/118, respiratory rate of 18, heart rate of 76, and oxygen saturation of 99% on room air. At the completion of the client's observation, client stated that numbness was "better" and stated that it was "almost gone." Client's blood pressure improved upon reassessments, and all other vitals were remained within normal limits. Client was provided with vaccine information packets and encouraged to seek follow-up care or emergency care if symptoms become more severe later in the evening. EMS was denied by client, no medication or other interventions were indicated or administered. Client departed facility by ambulation to private care at 1253 in positive disposition. EMT reported to lead nurse about client's status after client left facility already. Lead nurse educated EMT regarding high blood pressure referral to EMS. But EMT  stated client denied EMS.
HISTORY: History of Deep Vein Thrombosis and  Hypertension

DVT (LEFT CALF); PULMONARY EMBOLISM (BOTH LUNGS); ATRIAL FIBRILLATION; BLOOD CLOT IN RIGHT VENTRICLE; This spontaneous report was received from a consumer (patient's wife) and concerned a 68 year old male. The patient's weight was 250 pounds and was obese (body mass index 40) and sedentary. His height was not provided. The patient's concurrent conditions included high blood pressure, and 2 gout attacks in the last 8 months. The last gout attack was 2 weeks ago in the left foot. There was no history of clots or atrial fibrillation. He had a strong family history of thrombosis: his father had 2 episodes of deep vein thrombosis and his mother had a pulmonary embolism. No testing to identify any familial clotting issues have been performed. The patient developed a cough starting 29-MAR-2021 and, prior to vaccination, took a COVID-19 test on 31-MAR-2021 which was negative. On 02-APR-2021 a rapid COVID-19 test also came back negative.  The patient received covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s (suspension for injection, route of admin not reported, batch number: 043A21A, and expiry: UNKNOWN) on 02-APR-2021 at approximately 19:00 in the left arm for prophylactic vaccination. Concomitant medications included amlodipine, hydrochlorothiazide, and losartan for high blood pressure. On 03-APR-2021, the patient's cough persisted but had not worsened and he developed pain in the ribs on the right. His wife checked his pulse, which seemed fast and irregular. His respiratory rate was 22 breaths per minute and his oxygen saturation with a home pulse oximeter was in the 70s. He was not in distress at the time. The patient called his physician and the doctor suggested to go to Emergency room. The patient went to Emergency room at approximately 10:00. An echocardiogram revealed a number of clots in the right ventricle which were "bouncing all around". He was also found to be in atrial fibrillation which the doctors said was secondary to the ventricular clots. Unspecified tests revealed a saddle pulmonary embolus and a deep vein thrombosis on the left.  He was diagnosed with deep vein thrombosis (left calf), pulmonary embolism (both lungs), blood clots in right ventricle and atrial fibrillation. Platelet count was not known by the reporter; it is unknown if  D-dimer and fibrinogen levels were performed.  He underwent emergency surgery at 19:00, during which most of the ventricular clots and the pulmonary embolism were removed. He was placed on heparin after the surgery. He spent 5 days in the Intensive Care Unit (ICU) and 2 additional days in the hospital. The patient was discharged from the hospital after 1 week and had recovered from the events of deep vein thrombosis (left calf), pulmonary embolism (both lungs), atrial fibrillation, and blood clots in right ventricle.  The action taken with covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s was not applicable. The reporter did not believe that the covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s had caused deep vein thrombosis (left calf), pulmonary embolism (both lungs), atrial fibrillation, and blood clot in right ventricle This report was serious (Hospitalization Caused / Prolonged, and Other Medically Important Condition).; Sender's Comments: V0:  a 68-year-old male experienced left deep vein thrombosis, saddle pulmonary embolism, right ventricular thrombosis, and atrial fibrillation, approximately 15 hours after receiving the Janssen COVID-19 vaccine for prevention of COVID-19 infection.  The patient has a history of hypertension, is obese (BMI 40) and has a strong family history of blood clots.  He tested negative for COVID 2 days before and the day of vaccine administration.  He developed a cough 4 days prior to vaccination. The morning after vaccination, he developed right rib pain; his heart rate was rapid and irregular, and oxygen saturation with home pulse oximeter was in the 70s.  Upon arrival in the emergency room, he was found to have clots in the right cardiac ventricle, a saddle pulmonary embolus, left deep vein thrombosis and new-onset atrial fibrillation.  He underwent surgery for removal of the ventricular clots and pulmonary embolism.  No laboratory details were provided.  Given the symptoms which pre-dated vaccine administration,  the short latency between the vaccine administration and the event, and multiple risk factors for embolism and thrombosis (family history, obesity, sedentary nature), the events are assessed as inconsistent with the causal association to immunization, per the WHO causality classification for adverse events following immunization. Therefore, company causality is considered not related to the Janssen COVID-19 vaccine.

After I drove up and got my shot, the people had me drive to the next parking lot and park.  We had to park every other space.  By the time I got parked, I started to feel dizzy.  I was afraid to tell anyone because I didn't want to go to the hospital.  At first, I felt extremely dizzy so that I would not have driven if I had been allowed.  Then, My heart then started to race for about 5 minutes before it started to calm down.  The person who gave me my shot wrote on my paper on my dashboard that I had to sit for 20 minutes after my shot.   I sat there for the whole 20 minutes and by the time I left, I felt much better, but it scared me it a bit.  I was told to beep my horn if I had a reaction, but I was afraid too.  I sat in my truck and waited to see if it got better or worse.  It did get better.  I was told by friends that I should report it so I am. I have been fine this week since that happened after the vaccination, without any dizziness or heart racing.  But, I am having pain in my left leg and I'm a little worried about that because people are reporting blood clots.  I think I have a vein that is bad in that leg, although I have never been diagnosed with it.   That area has caused me pain in the past but I am so used to it that I normally just ignore it.  There's just a spot on my left thigh that hurts where I think the veins are bad.  Since the vaccination, I have had more pain in that area.  I don't know if I need to be concerned with that.  I have been trying to wait that out too.
OTHER_MEDS: I wasn't taking any medications or dietary supplements.  I am a regular drinker of herbal teas but I can't remember if I had drank any.
HISTORY: Asthma, but I wasn't suffering from it at the time of the injection of the vaccine.  I was breathing fine.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Both my mother and father had their shots on the same day.  Mother (77) had mild fatigue the day after the shot with some arm soreness.  She was fine after about a day.  My father reported  arm soreness and fatigue that lasted about three days after the shot.  He thought he was rebounding from the shot and continued his usual activities.  Though, he started complaining of being "winded" and difficulty breathing.  He slept a lot and continued with fatigue and shallow breathing.  A week after his shot he felt he needed to go to the ER because of difficulty breathing and being exhausted after walking up a flight of stairs (we live in a raised ranch style house).
LAB_DATA: In the ER,  X-rays of his chest showed sizeable blood clots in both lungs as well as what appeared to be clotting in the aortic valve.   After 5 days in the hospital he was determined to be anemic.  They couldn't find a cause for the clots (no family history of blood clots).  He was put on Eloquis for the clotting, heart medication (carvedilol), pantoprazole (GERD), and low dose oxycodone for pain in his right lung.  Appointments with specialists and his PCP are ongoing since his release from the hospital.  An outpatient endoscopy and colonoscopy did not reveal signs of bleeding (which is what they were looking for to explain the anemia).  Appointments with a Vascular Surgeon and Cardiologist are forth-coming.  Patient seems to be improving some (as the blood clots are being addressed with the blood thinner), but he is not "out of the woods" so far as I can tell.  Breathing is  improved, fatigue has lessened a bit, but stamina is still a work in progress.

hypoaldosteronism, excessive fatigue; hirsutism, an increase of hair growing on pt's face and chest.; chronic migraines; menstrual irregularities; POTS, nausea, dizziness, fatigue, chest pain, trouble breathing, presyncope, tachycardia, heart palpitations, difficulty concentrating, unrefreshing sleep, vertigo, lowblood pressure, blurred vision visual disturbances; orthostatic intolerance (OI); she began to experience symptoms of autonomic dysfunction such as trembling, chaking, chest pressure, palpitations and headaches; stomach cramps, nausea, decreased appetite, cold and clammy extremities, heat intolerance; Information has been received regarding a case in litigation from a lawyer and referred to a currently adult female patient (pt.) of unknown age. Information on the pt's concurrent conditions, medical history or concomitant therapy was not reported. It was reported that she was happy and physically very active without autonomic issues, no tachycardia, and no orthostasis; she had met all expected developmental milestones to that point; she was a good student and was doing very well in her classes; and was very physically active and enjoyed spending time with her friends. On 05-NOV-2012 during a physical examination, the pt's pediatrician recommended that pt receive quadrivalent human papillomavirus (types 6,11,16,18) recomb. vaccine (GARDASIL) vaccine an on the same date (at the age of 14), and under the consent of pt's mother, the pt. was vaccinated with a first dose of quadrivalent human papillomavirus (types 6,11,16,18) recomb. vaccine (GARDASIL) for prevention of cervical cancer (lot#, expiration date, dose, route of administration and anatomical location were not reported). Soon after the pt. was vaccinated with the first dose, she developed symptoms of fatigue, dizziness, and nausea. Pt. and her parents noticed an increase of hair growing on pt's face and chest. On 04-FEB-2013 (at the age of 15), the pt. returned to the pediatrician's office to receive the second dose of quadrivalent human papillomavirus (types 6,11,16,18) recomb. vaccine (GARDASIL) for prevention of cervical cancer (lot#, expiration date, dose, route of administration and anatomical location were not reported). It was after this second shot of quadrivalent human papillomavirus (types 6,11,16,18) recomb. vaccine (GARDASIL) that pt. began to experience symptoms of dysautonomia, such as trembling, shaking, chest pressure, palpitations, and headaches. On 18-MAR-2013 and on 28-MARCH-2013, the pt. was taken to the hospital for episodes of chest pains, dizziness, and tachycardia (unclear if she was admitted to the hospital due to the events). As the months progressed, so did pt's injuries. She was seen by multiple physicians and specialists for her complaints which now included: dizziness; chest pains; trouble breathing; presyncope; tachycardia and heart palpitations; nausea and stomach cramps; decreased appetite; excessive fatigue; difficulty concentrating; unrefreshing sleep; vertigo; low blood pressure; blurry vision and visual disturbances; cold and clammy extremities; heat intolerance; chronic migraines; and menstrual irregularities. Therefore, it was claimed, that the pt. sustained autoimmune disease and other serious injuries, including but not limited to postural orthostatic tachycardia syndrome ("POTS"), orthostatic intolerance ("OI"), and autonomic dysfunction as a result of his quadrivalent human papillomavirus (types 6,11,16,18) recomb. vaccine (GARDASIL) injections. It was claimed that quadrivalent human papillomavirus (types 6,11,16,18) recomb. vaccine (GARDASIL) and its ingredients caused pt's autoimmune disease and other related injuries and resulted in her suffering from severe, debilitating, disabling and painful chronic injuries. As a result of her post-quadrivalent human papillomavirus (types 6,11,16,18) recomb. vaccine (GARDASIL) symptoms, pt. was unable to engage in normal activities that a normal teenager would enjoy. She had trouble keeping up with classes during her sophomore year of high school and did the majority of this grade at home. Pt. was unable to attend college classes on campus due to her extreme fatigue. Based upon her chronic and severe post-quadrivalent human papillomavirus (types 6,11,16,18) recomb. vaccine (GARDASIL) symptoms and adverse events as outlined above and the tests performed by dozens of medical providers, pt had been diagnosed with various medical conditions, including but not limited to POTS, OI, autonomic dysfunction, hypoaldosteronism, hirsutism, and chronic migraines. As a proximate result of vaccination, pt. had suffered and continued to suffer severe and permanent physical injuries and associated symptomology and had suffered severe and permanent emotional injuries, including pain and suffering. Pt. also had a substantial fear of suffering additional and ongoing harms, including but not limited to now being at an increased risk of cancer and future symptoms and harms associated with her autoimmune disease as a result of her exposure to quadrivalent human papillomavirus (types 6,11,16,18) recomb. vaccine (GARDASIL). At the reporting time, she was not recover from the events. The reporter considered all events to be disabling and related to quadrivalent human papillomavirus (types 6,11,16,18) recomb. vaccine (GARDASIL).

Two days later, the patient experienced weakness, myalgia, nausea, dizziness, headache, shortness of breath, chest pain, increase in blood pressure, and a weigh loss of 20 pounds after 93 days. arm pain was not bad; face has been getting very red lately around the area where her face mask is specifically worn / redness around the site where the first Shingrix dose was administered; redness around the site where the first Shingrix dose was administered; small "pimple sore" the size of the head of a pin developing on her right arm / four little dots around the Shingrix injection site; small "pimple sore"; This case was reported by a consumer via call center representative and described the occurrence of pain in arm in a adult female patient who received Herpes zoster (Shingrix) for prophylaxis.   The patient's past medical history included shingles (Family History) (grandmother has shingles). Concurrent medical conditions included allergic reaction to wasp sting (patient had allergy to wasp sting).   In February 2021, the patient received the 1st dose of Shingrix (intramuscular). On an unknown date, less than a week after receiving Shingrix, the patient experienced pain in arm, red face, injection site erythema, pimples and pain. On an unknown date, the outcome of the pain in arm, red face, pimples and pain were recovered/resolved and the outcome of the injection site erythema was unknown.   It was unknown if the reporter considered the pain in arm, red face, injection site erythema, pimples and pain to be related to Shingrix.  Additional details were provided as follows: The patient was in early 60s. The age at vaccination was not reported. The patient stated she had a little reaction to the first Shingrix dose. The patient had small pimple sore the size of the head of a pin developing on her right arm a couple of days after receiving the first Shingrix dose. The patient further described the pimple sore as four little dots around the Shingrix injection site. This pimple sore lasted for a few weeks. The patient also reported that her face had been getting very red lately around the area where her face mask was specifically worn. She stated that this had lasted for two to three weeks. The patient also reported that she had arm pain that started the day of or the day after receiving the first Shingrix dose. This arm pain was not bad and only lasted a few days. The patient also described redness around the site where the first Shingrix dose was administered. She stated that this redness started about a week after receiving the first Shingrix dose. The patient also reported a medical history that she could not wear wool. The patient declined to provide any demographic or contact information out of privacy concerns. The patient was unable to provide the dosage and lot number/expiration date of the first Shingrix dose she received. The reporter did not consented to follow up.
CUR_ILL: Allergic reaction to wasp sting (patient had allergy to wasp sting)
HISTORY: Medical History/Concurrent Conditions: Shingles (grandmother has shingles)

Patient reported to medical clinic  24 hours after COVID 19 injection (03/19/2021) with symptoms of visual hallucinations, myalgia, rigors, headache, nausea, vomiting and dehydration.  At the time of arrival to the medical clinic, he had refractory nausea and vomiting after receiving Zofran earlier in the day at another clinical site. Medical treatment consisted of IV Fluid bolus with maintenance fluids, IV Phenergan for the nausea and vomiting, and IV Ketorolac for headache pain. His  symptoms resolved and he started to feel better so a clinical decision was made to discharge him home in the care of a close friend. He declined any other treatment modalities or medications at the time of the discharge.  The patient returned on 03/28/2021 with a right arm DVT proven on U/S. He was then started on anticoagulation therapy after specialist phone consult and will be closely followed.

headache; body ache; rough 12 hours of fever; This case was reported by a consumer via sales rep and described the occurrence of fever in a female patient who received Herpes zoster (Shingles vaccine) for prophylaxis.   The patient's past medical history included accident (tearing all the ligaments in leg plus and knee), chickenpox, breast cancer (Family History), shingles (about 5cm long and about 2 inches wide, running to her left side), pain (Pt felt a hot acupuncture needle being inserted directly into her nerve in lower back), influenza-like symptoms, joint pain, fever, nausea, headache, rash, surgery, stress, pruritus (got worse throughtout the day and evening and the next morning became intense) and low back pain. Previously administered products included Shingrix (received 1st dose on unknown date).   In April 2021, the patient received the 2nd dose of Shingles vaccine. In April 2021, less than a week after receiving Shingles vaccine, the patient experienced fever, headache and general body pain. On an unknown date, the outcome of the fever was recovered/resolved and the outcome of the headache and general body pain were unknown.   It was unknown if the reporter considered the fever, headache and general body pain to be related to Shingles vaccine.  Additional details were provided as follows: The patient was the reporter herself. The age at vaccination was not reported. The patient received 2nd dose of Shingrix and experienced fever of about 12 hours, headache and body ache. The reporter stated that, she was happy to know that she was protected against recurrence of virus. The reporter suggested that do not wait to receive shingles vaccine as she did. The reporter asked for shingles vaccine in past, but as flu season was coming, she was recommended to receive flu vaccine and was suggested to come back next month for shingles vaccine. The reporter stated that, the practitioner was not willing to co-administer the both vaccines. The reporter was suggested not to concerned much about shingles as she was recently turned 50. The reporter knew that the CDC had changed the age recommendations from 65 and older to 50 as the cases were becoming more frequent in youngers. The patient had family history of breast cancer including her late mother. The reporter mentioned that, two weeks before Christmas, patient felt itching on lower back which got worse and worse throughout the day and next morning became intense which was accompained by lower backache. The patient experienced shingles rash and went to Nurse practitioner and was prescribed antivirals and was sent home for rest. The reporter stated that, many friends and family have had much worse cases, including several who had the rash on their faces, and one friend whose mother had it affect her eye.  The most common complication of shingles is post-herpetic neuralgia (PHN). People with PHN have severe pain in the areas where they had the shingles rash after (at least 90 days) the rash clears up. The pain from PHN usually goes away in a few weeks or months; however, for some people, the pain from PHN can last for years and may interfere with their everyday life.
HISTORY: Medical History/Concurrent Conditions: Accident (tearing all the ligaments in leg plus and knee); Breast cancer; Chickenpox; Fever; Headache; Influenza-like symptoms; Joint pain; Low back pain; Nausea; Pain (Pt felt a hot acupuncture needle being inserted directly into her nerve in lower back); Pruritus (got worse throughtout the day and evening and the next morning became intense); Rash; Shingles (about 5cm long and about 2 inches wide, running to her left side); Stress; Surgery

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received my second dosage of the Moderna vaccine March 17.   A couple of hours afterwards I began to cough without stopping for about 20 minutes. I later went to bed and during the middle of the night I felt so sick; my who body was on fire with great pain with a temperature of 104. The shoulder where the injection was taken had swollen so big. I couldn't move. I had my husband to take me to the bathroom and back and put me in the bed. Then later on in the morning I got the chills; I was freezing; my husband had covered me up tight with my thick bed jacket and I had on flannels; I was still cold. All day Thursday was the same thing. I wanted a bunch of icy cold water (I never drink cold water). The water helped. That night was the same so bad I began crying. I thought of going to the ER but wanted to see how the morning turns out. Around 5:00 am Friday morning I noticed the pain and the chills had ceased; by 6:00 am I really felt good. Whatever that was (side effects)   Around 4 days later I developed the Covid Arm.  Nasty redness, blueish,  shoulder with rash and shoulder very painful and painful to touch.  My could move my arm at all; the should was hard and stiff and felt exactly like after my shoulder surgery I had years ago.  I followed up with my ortho doctor who told me that looking at my x-rays  it looks as if the vaccine took an effect on my rotator cuff. She also stated that sometimes when given a shot,  the provider should make sure the shot is given in a specific area and this time it may have hit my rotator cuff.  She gave a shot of cortisone, I forget what she said was added also to it.  My are began to move for use but I'm still not there yet.  It still hurts and very painful if I trying moving my arm in certain areas, the shoulder bone cracks with each movement.  I go to see another ortho surgeon on Tues 20th.
OTHER_MEDS: multiple vitamins for women w/bone & immune support , calcium w/vitamin d, amlodpine besylate, latanoprost, atorvastatin, calcium, finacea

Woke with up chest, arm and jaw pain on 03/21/2021. Presented to the ED. Her initial EKG was negative for any acute changes but her troponin was elevated. Cardiology was consulted. Her echo was negative for cardiomyopathy or hypertrophy. But after her troponin continued to rise she was taken to the cath lab to look for ischemia. Her cardiac angiography was negative for obstructive disease, and coronary arteries were completely normal. Had low magnesium and potassium- so started on oral supplementation. Discharged on 03/22/2021 with nitroglycerin (which was not helpful and made her feel worse/nauseated) and to follow up with outpatient cardiac MRI and cardiology. This imaging revealed significant myocardial edema consistent with myocarditis.   04/01/2021 Per Cardiology: -Given that the patient had covid 19 back in November 2019 I believe she may have had a low yield subacute myocardial infection at that time that was somehow exacerbated by her 1st covid vaccine. Therefore, after some consideration and careful discussion I am advising against the 2nd vaccine at this time.  -No physical exercise for 6 months given her current myocarditis and family hx of sudden cardiac death -May trial PRN NSAIDS for pain relief -Recommend birth control and no pregnancy until at least after her follow up cMRI  -Follow up in 6 months with cMRI prior

Slight temperature returned the next day (99.8), and no additional symptoms so far after a week.
Anaphylaxis - throat swelling

*** Symptoms - Headache - 30 mins after shot - lips tingling some - fatigued and body aches ***** Shortness of breath that gradually became severe over a 24 hour period. Referred to Emergency Department by physician for evaluation. Pulmonary embolism ruled out - diagnosed with  reactive airway disease with acute reaction exacerbation due to virus  and dyspnea at Emergency Department.  Been severely SOB unable to talk without gasping until 4/14/21 - Eliquis was increased to 5mg twice  - along with the Prednisone and Ventolin inhaler - Now able to talk small conversations, but walking short distances still causes respiratory problems and strain on body.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: ? Prior to anything, I have never been allergic to anything all my life and all of a sudden, I am allergic to almost everything I touch, eat and places I go. ? I have constant red rashes that appear  ? My face has been swollen for 39 days now and has not gone back to normal once since this all started.  ? During the weekend of March 6th, I was outside in my yard mulching, pulling out dead plants and planting new ones.  ? March 8th, 2021, I woke up with a swollen LEFT forearm. Went to urgent care. Told to ice and take Aleve. ? On March 9, 2021, I woke up with a swollen face only on LEFT side and went back to urgent care and gave me prednisone 6 days to take.  ? On March 12th, my arm was healing but my face was not and ended up swollen on both sides so I went to a different urgent care and they started me on antibiotics but didn?t not have me treated for anything specific because they were unsure what was happening and recommended to see an allergist.  ? On March 15th, is saw an allergist. He said the swollen arm and face were from an allergic reaction so they did round one of allergy testing for environmental, molds, cats/dogs and some food categories since I thought it was from yard work. I tested positive on almost all 80 tests and had to go back on March 17 for the second round of allergy testing and the final results.  ? On March 17th, I finished round two of allergy testing and was mostly positive on everything. The 8 food categories I was only positive for two, soybean and peanuts.  ? I decided to sign up for allergy drops rather than the shots twice a week. In the meantime, of waiting for the drops to get made I was put on more predisone, allergra, and one tablet of hydroxyzine hcl 25mg at night.  ? A week late my face was still swollen and nothing was working. I called the doctor office and they said to double the hydroxyzine at night. ? On March 29th, my face was still EXTREMELY swollen so we did a CT scan. Had bad sinus infection. He removed the Allegra and put me on one Clemastine 2.68mg in the morning. He then sent me for blood work. I went that evening.  ? On March 31st, I went to get my hair done with the same hair stylist and with the same bleach I?ve been doing on my hair for 13+ years with. I have never once broken out or had a reaction but this time I did. My face, neck, chest was boiling red of a rash.  ? On April 5th, I went back and all my blood work was good. However, my face was STILL swollen and hadn?t gone back to normal in since March 7. I stayed on the same meds and started the allergy drops.  ? On April 12th, I went to get my nails done and broke out in another red boiling rash with another reaction. Been going to the same lady for 10+ years and never had a reaction or rash.  ? On April 13th, I went to the dentist and got a filling re done and molded for a retainer to get whitening gel. After the numbing shot and molding, I immediately broke out in a red rash all over, face swelled up way bigger than it already was and within 30 mins couldn?t breathe well and had to use my epi pen. I was able to breathe again.  ? On April 14th, I went back to the doctor because I had a red-hot rash all over my body that will not go away and the doctor said it?s unknown of what?s exactly going on right now. I got put on more prednisone for the rash. I go back on April 21st for a follow up.  38 DAYS LATER and my face has NOT ONCE gone back to normal and rashes are still appearing each day. I have went from being allergic to absolutely nothing to what it feels like almost everything. Every time I eat this week something swells up more and rashes appear more red. No medicine is working. It?s getting out of control at this point.
LAB_DATA: March 29th: CT Scan- everything clear except bad sinus infection  March 29th: Comprehensive Metabolic Panel Urinalysis, Complete W/Reflex to CU TSH W/Reflex to Free T4 C-Reactive Protein Immunoglobulin A Immunoglobulin E Immunoglobulin G Immunoglobulin M CBC (Includes Diff/PLT) ALL blood work came back good.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient received Moderna COVID-19 vaccination. About 10 minutes after injection patient was not looking well. I escorted him to a private area where he continued to be light headed, pale in appearance, and communicated in short sentences. While sitting patients BP was 60/40 and pulse was thready. He was placed on the floor with legs elevated and EMS called. Lungs were clear and normal, heart tones normal as well. No sings of angioedema at any point of his episode. 3 minutes later BP increased to 80/60 with a stronger radial pulse, and a recheck again about 5 minutes later resulted in a BP of 110/72 with regular radial pulse. EMS arrived and assessed patient. He refused transfer to hospital. He was given time, water, and a small meal as he had not eaten or drank much of anything through is night shift. After about 30 minutes he was able to ambulate through the auditorium and stated he was feeling much better. We encouraged him to take the remainder of the day off but he declined and returned to work. He stated he would return if any symptoms were to reoccur or if he had any concerns. He will have his next dose of vaccine in clinic.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: At 3:40 am 4/8/21 my dog woke me to go outside. As I walked down the stairs, I was happy  I felt perfectly normal as I had heard so many side effects. My arm was sore but that was all. After a few minutes I went back upstairs and became incredibly nauseas and light headed. It was more overwhelming than any feeling like that in my life. I wasn?t sure if I was going to vomit or faint. I rushed in bed and was breathing very heavily in my nose and out of my mouth focusing on this awful feeling to pass. After a few minutes my right shoulder started to tingle and feel numb. The sensation started working its way down my right arm then began on the left side. The tingling/numb sensation went all the way to my fingertips and I lost movement in both of my hands. I could still feel touch but I had no movement in my fingers. After about five minutes I slowly regained movement in my fingers and the tingle/numb sensation moved slowly back up both my arms in the same manner it began. After roughly ten minutes this episode had entirely passed and I went back to sleep. When I woke around 7am I felt relatively normal, just minor tiredness and headache. Around 1:00pm I developed a fever of 100.7 and went to bed for the day about 6:00pm on 4/8/21. When I woke Friday 4/9/21 I felt entirely back to normal.  My husband said if I hadn?t regained movement of my fingers when I did, he was going to take me to the ER because it was so bizarre and scary. While the episode was at its peak, my husband gave me two Tylenol.
OTHER_MEDS: Pulmicort, Zoloft, vitamin D, probiotics, multi vitamin

Within 15-minutes of vaccination, the patient reported headache, nausea, and malaise. Paramedics evaluated the patient on-site. The patient was hypertensive (229/129). EKG demonstrated NSR, rate 85 bpm, no ST elevation. Paramedics transported the patient to Emergency Department. In the ED, the patient developed centralized chest pain, diaphoresis, and right jaw pain, but denies shortness of breath, nausea/vomiting, focal weakness, fever or chills. The patient remained hypertensive (184/85). Physician administered 325mg PO Aspirin, 0.2mg PO Clonidine, and 1 inch topical Nitroglycerin. The labs and imaging did not present evidence of myocardial infarct or intracranial hemorrhage. Due to symptoms on presentation, the patient was admitted to rule out ACS. Upon admission, the patient stated the chest pain "comes and goes", but is not currently having any chest discomfort. Admitting physician administered 5mg PO Amlodipine, 5mg PO Lisinopril, labetalol 10mg  IV, and prophylactic Lovenox. As of 4/16, the patient had not been discharged, but their hypertensive urgency and chest pain have resolved and will be treated outpatient. Internist planning patient's discharge.

Patient is a 71-year-old female with history of hypertension, hyperlipidemia, and obesity who presents with complaint of acute onset shortness of breath.  She reports she was walking around her house earlier when she suddenly became short of breath.  She denies any chest pain, numbness or tingling but states that shortness of breath persisted.  She denies any tobacco, alcohol or drug use and states she has never had any symptoms similar to this before.  Denies any lung disease or heart disease previously.  She does have hypertension and hyperlipidemia and is on metoprolol and rosuvastatin respectively which she reports good compliance.  Denies family history of MI or strokes.  She also denies other symptoms such as nausea, vomiting, abdominal pain, fevers or lower extremity edema.  In the ED vitals were found to be within normal limits.  EKG was obtained showing diffuse T wave inversions, right bundle branch block, no ST changes, no hypertrophy.  Troponin found to be elevated at 0.137, creatinine elevated at 1.3, BUN 26.  Chest x-ray was within normal limits.  Otherwise lab work was unremarkable.  She was given aspirin and Nitropaste Hospital Course:         Patient was admitted to the medical floor and remained hemodynamically stable throughout her stay. She actually remained asymptomatic and had no further shortness of breath. She was not hypoxic, at no point required supplemental oxygen. Her troponins however continued to uptrend to 0.389. Cardiology consulted, she was medically optimized with increased statin dose, therapeutic lovenox, and aspirin. Original plan was for cardiac catheterization. However, a d-dimer was ordered which returned elevated to 13.7. CTA was performed which revealed extensive bilateral pulmonary emboli with large clot burden and concern for right heart strain. Echocardiogram showed mildly dilated and hypokinetic RV with mild diastolic dysfunction with impaired relaxation. She was deemed not to be candidate for EKOS. Troponin elevation was felt to be type II NSTEMI 2/2 PE.  PE was classified as unprovoked as she has no definite risk factors for this: no prior DVT/PE, no family history of clotting disorder, no evidence of malignancy (UTD with cancer screenings and visits PCP q6m for health maintenance), no cell line abnormalities, no prolonged immobility or long trips or surgeries, no trauma, no hormone or steroid therapies or even antidepressants. She is obese, and has mild CKD. She tested negative for COVID-19 by antigen testing. The only identifiable change in her health habits recently was receiving the first COVID-vaccine dose on 3/18. We discharged her with Eliquis with instructions to taper from 10BID to 5BID after 7 days. As she will be on anticoagulation, the benefit will likely outweigh the risk of receiving the second COVID dose.  She will follow up with her PCP and hematology/oncology.
LAB_DATA: 03/28/2021:  Chest CTA - Extensive bilateral pulmonary emboli with overall large clot burden and suggestion of pulmonary arterial hypertension and right heart strain. 03/29/2021:  Cardiac echocardiogram - Conclusion - The left ventricle is normal size. The left ventricular systolic function is normal. LVEF is 60-65%. There is normal LV segmental wall motion. Mild diastolic dysfunction is present (impaired relaxation pattern). Right ventricle is mildly dilated. Right ventricle is mildly hypokinetic. Trace tricuspid regurgitation. 003/29/2021:  Vascular ultrasound:  Conclusion - This study is negative for thrombus in the deep and superficial venous system in both lower extremities Labs:  03/28/2021:  D-Dimer 13.7  Troponin 0.389  BNP:  3430

Received shot around 10:00am April 12th, by 12:00pm (beginning of work shift)I experienced a headache and took Advil, figured it was menstrual related since it started the same day. By 5:00 my body started to feel aches and chills but was very mild. By 5:30-5:45 I took a midal for the pain I was experiencing, more severe muscle/ back aches and chills. By 6:30 I went home early from work because symptoms were getting worse and it was hard to continue my shift. Once arriving home around 8 pain continue to progress but I figured I just needed to lay down and rest. By 9 I had soup but could barley finish due to pain. I continued to monitor my temperature because I was experiencing chills even though I had my heater on etc. by 10:00-10:30 my temperature went all the way up to 101.2 and I was concerned so I called 911. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient was given first dose of pfizer vaccine at approximately 3:20 pm. At 3:24 pm she developed a mild, red rash that was not raised on her chest and back. She did not have a generalized rash or itching at that time but within 20 minutes she developed itching to the area affected, with no breathing difficulty or throat swelling noted. VS were checked and within normal limits at the time the event started and 15 minutes afterward. After 30 minutes, she stated she felt her skin on her neck was "tight," and after 45 minutes she developed mild swelling on the left forearm. No breathing difficulty, no oropharyngeal edema or generalized hives or itching were present at any time. EMS was offered and called at 4:13 pm as symptoms seemed to progress and BP became elevated. EMS arrived 4:23 pm. She was given 50 mg Benadryl IM and transported to hospital for observation out of an abundance of caution.

Store manager was contacted to help assess reporting through Incident reporting process.  His BP was 118/82 after spending a few minutes with him and giving him water.  He had a sweaty forehead and sat with us for a bit. I did offer to call an ambulance and administer Benadryl.  Patient declined.  He mentioned fainting with blood donations in the past, never with vaccines.  We discussed for second shot we will stand nearby ready for fainting again, or receiving the shot at an MD office in prone (lying down) position.  There was no answer to a follow-up phone call the next morning.
CUR_ILL: None reported.  Discussed fainting with blood donations in past.

Patient presented after falling on February 5 with injury to her scalp.  She apparently also fell on 2/4/21.  Family was uncertain as to whether patient loss consciousness.  According to family, patient has been weak over the last day or 2 with no other complaints aside from some diarrhea. EMS was notified PM Feb 5, and the patient was found to have atrial fibrillation with elevated heart rate to the 160s and hypoxic to the low 80% range on room air. She had a low-grade temperature and elevated respiratory rate according to EMS.  Evaluation in the ED demonstrated bilateral chest infiltrates on chest x-ray (right greater than left), elevated heart rate with atrial fibrillation, and back pain. Imaging demonstrated a T11 compression fracture (possibly new), elevated pro-calcitonin (2.80 ng/mL) and elevated troponin (1.45 ng/mL). Her venous blood gas showed mild hypoxemia (7.39/25/41/33/57), and head CT did not show acute changes and her cervical CT was negative for fracture. Pelvic x-ray did not show fracture. She was covid positive.  Admitted for acute hypoxemic respiratory failure and severe sepsis secondary to COVID-19 pneumonia and acute metabolic encephalopathy.  Received 3 days of remdesivir and 4 days of IV dexamethasone.  Also ceftriaxone was given 4 days for possible UTI.  Goal of care switched to inpatient hospice on 2/8/21.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Got the vaccine,  had no problems at all.  He woke up the next morning on 3/24/21 with extreme pain in his legs, buttocks area, arms, and all muscles for some reason he got quite a bit of pain in his right hand and wrist.  He was spared any pain or discomfort in his left hand which is his dominant hand.  All of his limbs are very sore, and has a difficult time and having the feeling that he could not use a lot of his muscles.  He enjoys walking a couple of miles, bike riding, and push ups and he's not able to do that anymore and very limited in his mobility since his vaccine.  He now he cannot get in a car due to having difficulty lifting his legs, he has to use his hands to get his legs in the car now.  Getting up and down from a sitting position is also more difficult since the vaccine.  He found that bedrest is not what he needs and has to exercise as much as he can, and waking up in the morning is the worst part of the pain that he has, and a little bit better by moving around, and then it returns to the same in the morning.   He is not able to walk fast or as far as he used to before.  He went to the doctor for his physical and he checked him out and the blood tests which showed no inflammation but otherwise were normal other than some anemia, which they felt came from the vaccine.    Now this has caused depression for himself and his wife as they are not able to do the things that they used to be able to do, camping, vacationing and doing yard work as they used to be able to do before the vaccine.
OTHER_MEDS: Vitamin D3, Finasteride, Terazosin, Lutein, Melatonin.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: After receiving her second dose, patient experienced lightheadedness and reported she "felt like she was going to pass out." She also reported nausea. We provided her with a trash can and a bottle of water and asked her to wait in the waiting room for at least 30 minutes to be monitored. Her breathing was stable throughout, and she did not lose consciousness. Pt stayed for at least 30 minutes until she felt better and was okay to drive home. We called her later in the day to check on her and she reported feeling better but had a headache and was laying down.

I went to my eye doctor for my annual exam. They noticed I had a blood vessel break in my retnea so they sent me to a specialist. I didn?t think anything about it until my husband came home from his second shot and his blood vessel had popped in his eye. My husbands you could see right away mine was at the back of my eye and could not be seen. Once I saw his it hit me that it could of been from the shot, too coincidental!
OTHER_MEDS: Apple cider vinegar gummies, elderberry, allergy,probiotic

No other symptoms, rash was very  itchy  & after 4 days had NP look at rash  & was diagnosed with shingles. Previous history of chicken pox , never received shingles vaccine . Was out on 7 day Acyclovir x TID .  Have autoimmune disorder of type I diabetes.
OTHER_MEDS: humalog insulin via pump  losartan 25 mg qd ezetimibe 10 mg qd calcium + vit d  qd D3 25 mcg  qd vit B complex qd

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The side effects I'm experiencing didn't start until about 2 days later.  It started out as pain at the injection site with extremely bad dizziness that has gotten worse each day. On day 4 after the injection I noticed a full pain in my left thumb area. The same side as the injection. I didn't think anything of it but as the hour's and days went by it continued and continues to get worse. The best way I could explain it is it feels like when your hand falls asleep without the pins and needles. Yesterday I ended up having to go to the ER. My issue with my left thumb area started to get much worse. I couldn't hold things in my left hand and started to radiate up my arm. It was the weirdest feeling I can't really explain it other than being slightly numb and very week. I wasn't able to move my hand much at all. They gave me a cat scan but they never called me back to be seen or to give me my results. I was there for 8 hours and was never called back to be seen. I had to leave this morning before I was seen because I didn't have anyone to watch son. Today is 8 days since I received my first covid shot and I still have major fatigue along with dizziness. I will start sweating profusely out of nowhere and then stops.  I've had a numb/metallic taste in my mouth for about 4-5 days as well. I feel like I'm in a complete fog and can't shake this feeling. I'm having trouble concentrating and remembering things. I'm drinking lots of water and trying to rest when I can but I'm still feeling terrible with no signs of this getting better. My doctor suggested I report this to you and I'm hoping and praying this goes away. Is there anything I can do or a specialist I could see? Thank you so much in advance.

One week after I received it, I noticed I've had shortness of breath. It's not bad, but it's more difficult for me to breath through my mask, especially when I'm talking. When I've been talking for a while, I can't quite catch my breath. Also, I've slightly lost taste. Food tastes a bit 'off,' and some items even taste bitter. I had cake the other day, and, to my disappointment, it was bitter (my family said it tasted fine. It was just me). Also, for two and a half weeks from the onset of they symptoms, I had intense flu-like symptoms. I felt achy all over and fatigued, which chills. I found it odd because it started so late and lasted so long. The flu-like symptoms are the only things that have subsided.
LAB_DATA: I saw an allergist to see if maybe all of these symptoms were caused by allergies, and he said no. I got a COVID test a week and half (On April 6th)  after the symptoms started, and it was negative.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pt is a 64yo F with no known PMH who presented today with Left side facial droop with left side neglect. She reports that around 1230, she felt like her knees became weak and she fell to the ground. She notes that the landlord found her and called EMS. Pt reports that she did not feel any other symptoms such as N/v, CP, dizziness, lightheaded, slurred speech, abd pain, visual changes, seizure like activity, incontinence, sore tongue, or SOB. It was noted by EMS that she had left side facial droop. Pt reports that she felt normal prior to this event and was able to do all ADLs and ambulate without assistance. She does not report any medical hx but admits to not seeing a PCP in years. She denies smoking and excessive etoh use as well as illicit drug use. She notes that she has a family hx of MIs with her brothers and sister all in the ages of 60. Her father had diabetes and HTN for which he passed from "GI blockage" and her mother passed from hemorrhage giving birth. She does not recall a family hx of stroke or abnormal bleeds.  In the ED, her vitals were significant for a BP 231/114. She had an NIH of 12 and a HCT was ordered showing right basal ganglia hemorrhage concerning for HTN cause. NSY has been called with patient started on cardene gtt and keppra. CBC significant for hgb 12.6 and CMP with K low at 3.1. EKG was obtained showing LVH with potential ischemia. Cardiology was called and noted that changes where likely in relation to LVH. A troponin was obtained and negative. Lastly, she has had a Head and neck CTA without evidence of Carotid artery blockage but an occlusion present at the distal P2 right PCA.

death Narrative: Patient passed away on April 13, 2021 at home at 1810 He was 72 years old had severe aortic stenosis and hypertension and had an aortic valve replacement (TAVR) at hospital on Jan 20, 2021. He was readmitted to hospital for shortness of breath which was evaluated from Feb 19 - Feb 21, 2021 I spoke with his daughter today. She was with him at home when he went to the bathroom and since he had not come out for some time, she knocked on the door and found him collapsed in the bathroom. She called 911, who did CPR, however he had passed away. He was referred to the coroner. He had his first Moderna vaccine on March 15, 2021 after which he had not had any side effects. He received his second dose on April 12, 2021 and had not mentioned any side effects other than mild abdominal discomfort. Daughter said his shortness of breath had been improving after his discharge from the hospital. He had not complained of chest pain, cough, fever, diarrhea, in the last few days. I paid condolences to daughter and told here we would be reviewing the case to see if there was any relationship to him receiving the Covid19 vaccine and that the case had already been referred to the coroners office.
